Name: fallopian tube mucinous adenocarcinoma
Definition: A fallopian tube adenocarcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells originating in glandular tissue

Name: fallopian tube clear cell adenocarcinoma
Definition: A fallopian tube adenocarcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells which have clear cytoplasm.
Synonym: Clear cell carcinoma of the fallopian tube

Name: fallopian tube papillary adenocarcinoma
Definition: A fallopian tube adenocarcinoma that is characterized by a papillary growth pattern.
Synonym: Papillary adenocarcinoma of the fallopian tube

Name: fallopian tube serous adenocarcinoma
Definition: A fallopian tube adenocarcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells originating in glandular tissue forming serous lesions.
Synonym: Papillary adenocarcinoma of the fallopian tube

Name: fallopian tube endometrioid adenocarcinoma
Definition: A fallopian tube adenocarcinoma that derives_from endometrial epithelial cells of glandular origin.

Name: obsolete metastatic endometrioid carcinoma
Definition: A fallopian tube adenocarcinoma that derives_from endometrial epithelial cells of glandular origin.
